      "description": "Stream acquisitions of 1,000 frames were acquired on a Ti-Eclipse inverted microscope (Nikon) with Spinning Disc unit CSU-X1 (Yokogawa) using a 100×/1.49 NA oil immersion objective (pixel size =  67 nm) and the 49002 ET – EGFP (Chroma) filter set with a 491 nm laser. Images were captured with the following settings: 100 ms exposure time and EM 10 MHz (100 V gain) on a QuantEM512C 512x512pixels 16bit (Photometrics) with the Perfect Focus System (Nikon) switched on. During imaging, cells were maintained under 5%CO2 and 37°C conditions using a Tokai Hit incubator.",
